docs.abstract: The acquisition of HotelTonight, a service for travelers seeking last-minute hotel bookings, expands Airbnb’s listings ahead of an expected initial public offering.
docs.snippet: The acquisition of HotelTonight, a service for travelers seeking last-minute hotel bookings, expands Airbnb’s listings ahead of an expected initial public offering.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Airbnb says it plans to acquire HotelTonight, a service for travelers seeking last-minute hotel bookings, in a deal that will expand the lodging-rental company’s portfolio with traditional and boutique hotel listings.

headline.main: Airbnb Acquires HotelTonight to Expand Travel Portfolio
headline.print_headline: Airbnb Moves to Expand Travel Portfolio

docs.abstract: The talks precede Uber’s initial public offering and may ease worries about how costly it is to develop autonomous vehicles.
docs.snippet: The talks precede Uber’s initial public offering and may ease worries about how costly it is to develop autonomous vehicles.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber is in talks to sell a stake in its self-driving technologies unit to SoftBank and other investors for as much as $1 billion, as the ride-hailing company prepares to go public, according to four people with knowledge of the matter.

headline.main: SoftBank and Other Investors May Buy $1 Billion Stake in Uber’s Self-Driving Cars
headline.print_headline: Uber in Talks To Sell Stake Before I.P.O.

docs.abstract: Food retailers and producers warn that supermarkets and food outlets would be the first to feel the impact of Britain crashing out of the European Union with no deal.
docs.snippet: Food retailers and producers warn that supermarkets and food outlets would be the first to feel the impact of Britain crashing out of the European Union with no deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Farmers, bakers and food producers have added their voices to warnings that Brexit could become a dinner plate issue. And they weren’t mincing words: they called Brexit a catastrophe and said they were too busy preparing for it to deal with any other business issues.

headline.main: The Post-Brexit Food Chain: ‘This Is Really, Really Scary’
headline.print_headline: Brexit Could Make Food Inglorious, Retailers Warn

docs.abstract: Sales of the British standby have soared so much that the country added it back to the basket of goods it uses to measure inflation. Now, distillers are looking to reach a global cocktail crowd.
docs.snippet: Sales of the British standby have soared so much that the country added it back to the basket of goods it uses to measure inflation. Now, distillers are looking to reach a global cocktail crowd.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Ever since European apothecaries began distilling gin and selling it as a cure-all in the 16th century, the juniper-flavored liquor has been revered as a medicine, vilified for fueling public disorder and consumed in a multitude of every-season cocktails.

headline.main: Gin’s Journey in Britain, From ‘Mother’s Ruin’ to a Hipster Drink
headline.print_headline: Once ‘Mother’s Ruin,’ Gin Now Lures Hipsters
